cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with image-to-image translation using Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new GAN model architecture and explores different optimization losses, which are related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI) research, making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. The paper uses publicly available datasets for experiments, which suggests that it may fall under the graphics (GR) sub-category. Finally, since the paper deals with image generation, it may also be relevant to multimedia (MM) research.
